   Method Overloading                               Method Overriding.
1) method name must be same.                        Method name must be same
2) Argument type must be different (at least 1).    Argument type must be same.
3) Method signature must be different.              Method signature must be same.
4) return type has no restriction.                  Return type must be the same but this rule
                                                    is applicable until 1.4 version only. From
                                                    1.5 version onwards co-variant return types
                                                    are allowed.
5) Access modifier has no restriction               Can't reduce the cope of access specifier
                                                    but we can increase.
6) Private, static and final method can be          Private, static and final methods can't be
   overloaded                                       overridden.
7) throws clause no restriction                     If child class method throws any checked
                                                    exception compulsory the parent class throws
                                                    same checked exception otherwise we will get
                                                    compile time error but there is no restriction
                                                    for checked exception.
8) Method resolution is always takes care by        Method resolution is always takes care by JVM
   compiler based on reference type                 based on runtime object
9) Also known as compile time polymorphism/static   Also known as run time polymorphism/non-static
   /early binding                                   /late binding